Privacy Policy for PSU Attendance App

Effective Date: [8/22/2025]

PSU Attendance App (“we”, “our”, or “us”) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our app. By using the app, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.

1. Information We Collect

We may collect the following information:

Student Information: Names, roll numbers, and class/folder .

Attendance Data: Records of attendance, including present, absent, and excused status.

Login Information: If accounts are required, email addresses or usernames for authentication.

Device Information: Device model, operating system version, and app usage data (collected anonymously for analytics if applicable).

2. How We Use Your Information

Your data is used solely for the purpose of:

Tracking attendance and generating reports for students and classes.

Displaying attendance statistics and summaries in the app.

Sending notifications or reminders related to attendance (if applicable).

Improving app functionality and user experience.

3. Data Sharing

We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties, except where required by law or for legal compliance.

4. Data Security

We take reasonable measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be reflected in the app, and the “Effective Date” will be updated. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.

6. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

